						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">AWJ wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">LoROM advantages:<br /><br /> - You have ROM, hardware registers, and (the first 8kB of) WRAM all in the same bank, so you need fewer 24-bit absolute addresses and 24-bit pointers, making your code marginally smaller and faster.<br /></div><br /><br />You can do that with HiROM too.  The upper half of each bank also gets mapped into the LoROM area.</div>

